article.headline: Lehigh 83, Haverford 39
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Kyle Nepture scored 20 points and Jose Olivero added 17 to lead Lehigh to an 83-39 victory over Haverford on Monday night. Neptune hit all four of his 3-point attempts and went 7-for-10 from the field for Lehigh (5-8), which won its eighth straight home game. Zahir Carrington added 10 points in a reserve role. Ray Brown had 11 points for Division III Haverford (2-6). Lehigh capitalized on Haverford's 26 percent shooting in the first half (6-of-23) to take a 47-20 lead. The Mountain Hawks shot 18-for-34 from the field in the first half and were 32-for-61 overall. Lehigh outrebounded Haverford 43-26. Haverford was 8-of-25 from the field in the second half.
